post_text: Congratulations to the December Edward Jones Student of the Month, Bethany Janzen. She is a senior at Aurora High School and is involved in FPS, golf and FBLA. Her nominating form read, "Bethany is a respectful and mature young lady who puts forth a lot of effort in the classroom. Bethany is involved in Future Problem Solving both as a student as well as a coach. Bethany serves as a Future Problem Solving coach for our sixth grade students. She volunteers her time each week to help the young students in the program. Bethany has a servant's heart as she shares her experiences and knowledge with our younger students. She is an outstanding student who exemplifies high morals, integrity and is well respected by her classmates, teachers and administration. She is also an active member of FPS and her church."
